<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF107-991-328  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 991 328.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>MIS Week  Dec 18 1989 v10 n50 p5(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Banks, Sears plunge into financial EDI services: integration ofpurchasing and payment sides will increase efficiency.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Iida, Jeanne.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Eight banks are joining with network provider Sears CommunicationsCo to offer a service that enables companies using EDI to automateentirely the payment segments of their purchasing cycles.andP;  Theservice is customized for each group of trading partners, andgenerates electronic payments to suppliers via a participatingbank.andP;  Automating payments virtually eliminates errors associatedwith rekeying data.andP;  The Sears system represents a step towardintegrating the purchasing side with the payments side of EDI,thereby increasing productivity and efficiency, and underscoresthe shift within the banking industry toward services based ontransaction processing.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Sears Communications Co. (automation).andO;Topic:     TrendsElectronic Data InterchangeBankingAccounts PayableFully Automated.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>